<br>
I've started an iksar shammy, and I'm having a blast. 200+ people in field of bone isn't unlikely, and it's just as unlikely that you won't be able to find a group. TONS of mobs, tons of people of mixed classes...and useful, powerful ones. we got tanks, we got snarers, we got nukers, healers, heavy melee damage dealers, and the most powerful dotters. along with the billion evil dark elves who will even out what we lack in the int-caster department.<br>
<br>
everyone's taking advantagde of the GREAT newbie quests cabilis has to offer, from curscale armor to bone chips. people are using tradeskills, already selling banded armor, etc.<br>
<br>
most people are nice...there's some ks'ing because everyone rushes every newbie spawn and claims it theirs, but ah well. at least we don't have to fight along with enemies like in gfay and other zones, it's all allies which feels nice. we can grow strong without being disturbed.<br>
<br>
pretty cool to have the continent for ourselves, kunark is well protected from lighties. we can level in peace and just wait for the invasion....a powerful stronghold like cabilis is impossible to intrude on.<br>
<br>
good people are in a tight situation, with only faydwer seemingly still in their posession. i was in gfay (started out with a good char then changed) and all people did was whine about how the good would die and had no chance at all. dunno about that, but as far as I could see it, all they would have would be gfay and some newbie dungeons like CB and Unrest.<br>
<br>
Evil seem to have 'taken over' the karanas, commons, oasis, down to swamp and jungle of course. neutral....not sure where they stand, but they seems to have the western part of the world for now.<br>
<br>
LOTS of people seem to be going evil. I heard reports of nektulos having 400+ newbies at once, and the 200+ in fob showed a similar sign.<br>
<br>
anyway that was my 2cp...this server is really fun, give it a try if ya haven't already. <p><br>
